1
00:02:07,877 --> 00:02:09,811
Do you believe in God?

2
00:02:12,782 --> 00:02:16,343
No, but I enjoy
the tranquility here.

3
00:02:39,208 --> 00:02:41,176
Want to check the gun?

4
00:02:44,046 --> 00:02:45,741
I trust you.

5
00:02:59,095 --> 00:03:05,728
Another quiet tear

6
00:03:05,801 --> 00:03:10,397
Streaks down my face

7
00:03:10,473 --> 00:03:19,006
Another night ofdesolation

8
00:03:23,085 --> 00:03:27,181
And solitude

9
00:03:27,256 --> 00:03:29,588
Just accept me

10
00:03:29,659 --> 00:03:35,120
For what I am

11
00:03:35,197 --> 00:03:38,689
Don't make promises

12
00:03:38,768 --> 00:03:44,400
That you won't keep

13
00:03:47,476 --> 00:03:53,415
Who needs dreams

14
00:03:53,482 --> 00:03:58,283
When we have each other

15
00:04:00,623 --> 00:04:05,117
Who needs tomorrow

16
00:04:05,194 --> 00:04:13,260
When we have today

17
00:07:17,987 --> 00:07:21,354
- I can't see.
- Your corneas are badly damaged.

18
00:07:21,423 --> 00:07:24,517
- Will I recover?
- Your sight will never be perfect.

19
00:07:24,593 --> 00:07:28,256
- My sight is so blurred!
- We can do an operation transplant.

20
00:07:28,330 --> 00:07:29,820
Will I be blind?

21
00:07:29,899 --> 00:07:32,663
Jenny, I'm Sergeant Chang.

22
00:07:32,735 --> 00:07:35,670
Do you remember
the murderer's face?

23
00:07:41,644 --> 00:07:44,010
Please, leave me alone.
I'm frightened.

24
00:07:44,079 --> 00:07:45,046
Calm down.

25
00:07:53,155 --> 00:07:57,023
SIX MONTHS LATE R

26
00:08:41,837 --> 00:08:43,862
Help! Help!

27
00:08:43,939 --> 00:08:45,065
Please help!

28
00:09:20,342 --> 00:09:21,604
Just go away.

29
00:09:21,677 --> 00:09:24,942
They're gone now.
Don't be afraid.

30
00:09:25,014 --> 00:09:26,879
I'll take you home.

31
00:09:31,520 --> 00:09:33,454
Jenny!

32
00:09:33,522 --> 00:09:36,184
How do you know my name?

33
00:09:36,258 --> 00:09:38,886
I've listened to you sing so often...

34
00:09:38,961 --> 00:09:41,361
Who are you?

35
00:09:41,430 --> 00:09:45,764
I feel as if I know you.

36
00:09:48,037 --> 00:09:49,527
I know you can't see too well.

37
00:09:49,605 --> 00:09:52,301
I've wanted to help,
but I never had the chance.

38
00:09:55,244 --> 00:09:59,010
In this world,
not everybody is untrustworthy.

39
00:10:00,249 --> 00:10:02,547
Will you let me help you
this time?

40
00:10:25,741 --> 00:10:27,333
Is it all right for me to leave?

41
00:10:35,651 --> 00:10:39,087
Stay calm.
Let me check it out.

42
00:10:44,059 --> 00:10:45,117
It's only a cat.

43
00:10:45,194 --> 00:10:48,459
It often sneaks in
and scratches my furniture.

44
00:10:48,530 --> 00:10:50,259
What a pain!

45
00:11:15,724 --> 00:11:17,692
- Why did you turn off the light?
- You can see?

46
00:11:20,262 --> 00:11:22,230
I only see shadows.

47
00:11:22,297 --> 00:11:25,755
It was better last month.
I could see images.

48
00:11:25,834 --> 00:11:28,769
Turn on the light.
It makes me feel safer.

49
00:11:40,449 --> 00:11:42,417
What are you doing now?

50
00:11:42,484 --> 00:11:43,883
Looking at this scarf.

51
00:11:50,826 --> 00:11:56,025
It's got my blood stains on it.

52
00:11:56,098 --> 00:12:00,501
The man who shot me
wrapped it over my eyes.

53
00:12:00,569 --> 00:12:02,730
I'll never forget that.

54
00:12:02,805 --> 00:12:07,299
- Would you like some tea?
- No, thanks.

55
00:12:07,376 --> 00:12:09,742
It won't take a minute.
Please, sit.

56
00:12:09,812 --> 00:12:11,643
I'll put some music on.

57
00:12:13,315 --> 00:12:19,618
Another quiet tear

58
00:12:19,688 --> 00:12:24,489
Streaks down my face

59
00:12:24,560 --> 00:12:29,122
Another night of desolation

60
00:12:29,198 --> 00:12:33,430
And solitude

61
00:12:37,339 --> 00:12:43,744
Just accept me

62
00:12:43,812 --> 00:12:48,545
For what I am

63
00:12:48,617 --> 00:12:52,951
Don't make promises

64
00:12:53,021 --> 00:12:58,254
That you won't keep

65
00:13:01,230 --> 00:13:06,463
Who needs dreams...

66
00:13:06,535 --> 00:13:10,801
Relax! You look exactly like
what you are, an undercover agent.

67
00:13:10,873 --> 00:13:13,706
Lighten up,
or it'll be an open secret.

68
00:13:15,544 --> 00:13:17,444
Come on.

69
00:13:17,513 --> 00:13:19,003
Smile!

70
00:13:23,452 --> 00:13:26,421
Now you look like something
out of a nuthouse.

71
00:13:31,660 --> 00:13:34,857
Chang, this guy Eddie's
a lunatic. Be careful.

72
00:13:34,930 --> 00:13:37,899
Same to you, pal.

73
00:13:37,966 --> 00:13:39,593
Watch your ass!

74
00:13:50,779 --> 00:13:54,476
Eddie, sorry to keep you waiting.

75
00:13:54,550 --> 00:13:56,780
- Who the hell is that?
- He's a good buddy.

76
00:13:56,852 --> 00:13:58,911
- Say hello to Eddie.
- Eddie.

77
00:13:58,987 --> 00:14:00,750
Search him!

78
00:14:03,759 --> 00:14:06,193
Eddie, what's with the security?

79
00:14:06,261 --> 00:14:08,286
It's not our filrst deal.

80
00:14:12,367 --> 00:14:14,062
Maybe he looks familiar.

81
00:14:14,136 --> 00:14:19,597
Here's $200,000.
We'll check the guns filrst.

82
00:15:00,849 --> 00:15:02,646
What are you guys doing?

83
00:15:02,718 --> 00:15:04,811
Nothing special, offilcer.
A reunion.

84
00:15:04,886 --> 00:15:06,786
Open the trunk.

85
00:15:06,855 --> 00:15:08,254
Open it!

86
00:15:08,323 --> 00:15:10,291
Now!

87
00:15:15,263 --> 00:15:17,231
Damn you!
You set me up, didn't you?

88
00:15:17,299 --> 00:15:19,563
Are you a cop?

89
00:15:19,635 --> 00:15:21,227
Talk!

90
00:15:23,405 --> 00:15:28,775
I'm no cop!
I didn't betray you.

91
00:15:28,844 --> 00:15:31,142
Then how come he's here?

92
00:15:31,213 --> 00:15:34,080
He's no cop!
I stake my life on it, Eddie!

93
00:15:34,149 --> 00:15:36,344
Lying bastard,
I shouldn't have trusted you!

94
00:15:36,418 --> 00:15:37,942
The guy's a cop.
I recognize him!

95
00:15:38,020 --> 00:15:39,920
You've got it wrong.

96
00:15:52,534 --> 00:15:55,094
Chang, I'll get him!

97
00:16:05,547 --> 00:16:06,479
That shithead!

98
00:17:24,526 --> 00:17:26,460
Don't move!

99
00:17:35,103 --> 00:17:37,799
Goddamn mess, assho--

100
00:17:37,873 --> 00:17:39,534
Finish your sentence.

101
00:17:39,608 --> 00:17:42,076
Ass... assho--

102
00:17:48,183 --> 00:17:51,277
Inspector Li, the suspect
Eddie Hung held a hostage...

103
00:17:51,353 --> 00:17:53,344
in a crowded trolley car...

104
00:17:53,421 --> 00:17:55,355
Could you see him clearly?

105
00:17:55,423 --> 00:17:56,617
- Could you?
- Yes.

106
00:17:56,691 --> 00:17:58,921
- Why did you shoot?
- Instinct.

107
00:17:58,994 --> 00:18:01,690
Did you consider the safety
of the passengers?

108
00:18:01,763 --> 00:18:03,253
Did you sound any warning
before you shot?

109
00:18:03,331 --> 00:18:04,423
Insuffilcient time.

110
00:18:04,499 --> 00:18:06,831
The hostage had
a coronary thrombosis.

111
00:18:06,902 --> 00:18:09,427
She died of a heart attack.

112
00:18:09,504 --> 00:18:11,597
Her family has registered
an offilcial complaint.

113
00:18:11,673 --> 00:18:14,506
- You're responsible for her death.
- That's crazy

114
00:18:14,576 --> 00:18:16,874
How could I know she had
a heart condition?

115
00:18:16,945 --> 00:18:19,311
I've been on Eddie Hung's case
for seven months.

116
00:18:19,381 --> 00:18:23,147
The guy was a maniac.
He'd shoot anybody for any reason.

117
00:18:23,218 --> 00:18:25,482
Should I have waited
until he killed her?

118
00:18:26,721 --> 00:18:29,986
You forget
I'd just seen him kill a cop.

119
00:18:30,058 --> 00:18:32,583
Who's responsible
for that cop's death?

120
00:18:38,567 --> 00:18:41,934
Fine! Do whatever you want.

121
00:18:42,003 --> 00:18:45,302
I'm used to all sorts
of complaints.

122
00:18:45,373 --> 00:18:47,671
One more makes no difference.

123
00:19:05,994 --> 00:19:07,052
Catch!

124
00:19:16,705 --> 00:19:19,640
- How's the action hand?
- Pretty useless.

125
00:19:23,812 --> 00:19:25,211
Better use it more.

126
00:19:25,280 --> 00:19:27,214
It won't help.

127
00:19:28,650 --> 00:19:31,517
A one-handed killer's
out of the action.

128
00:19:33,755 --> 00:19:36,588
I've had my day.

129
00:19:44,399 --> 00:19:45,661
His name is Tony Weng.

130
00:19:45,734 --> 00:19:49,170
He works with a drug ring
in Central America.

131
00:19:49,237 --> 00:19:52,502
- Who wants him dead?
- No questions. Take it or leave it.

132
00:19:56,578 --> 00:19:59,547
- 1 .5 million.
- Seems high.

133
00:20:01,750 --> 00:20:03,377
This is my last hatchet job.

134
00:20:04,920 --> 00:20:09,653
All right, it's a deal.
Money's no object.

135
00:20:14,262 --> 00:20:18,096
These guns are clean.
No serial numbers.

136
00:20:18,166 --> 00:20:20,031
Untraceable.

137
00:20:20,101 --> 00:20:22,365
Explosive head bullets.
Your favorite.

138
00:20:44,726 --> 00:20:47,160
Easy to pick up, hard to put down.

139
00:20:48,396 --> 00:20:49,988
Want to change your mind?

140
00:21:11,419 --> 00:21:12,443
Why take this job?

141
00:21:16,758 --> 00:21:22,162
If she doesn't have
a cornea transplant soon...

142
00:21:22,230 --> 00:21:24,596
she might lose her sight forever.

143
00:21:24,666 --> 00:21:26,930
There's a cornea bank
in Hong Kong...

144
00:21:27,002 --> 00:21:29,266
but it's always empty.

145
00:21:29,337 --> 00:21:34,138
When a donation does come in,
someone else gets it filrst.

146
00:21:34,209 --> 00:21:36,336
So we're going to try abroad.

147
00:22:01,736 --> 00:22:04,068
I have to leave you
for a few days.

148
00:22:04,139 --> 00:22:08,098
When I return, I'll take you
overseas for surgery.

149
00:22:10,912 --> 00:22:13,312
You will come back, right?

150
00:22:14,582 --> 00:22:16,174
I promise.

151
00:22:32,333 --> 00:22:35,359
Today is the Dragon Boat Festival.

152
00:22:35,437 --> 00:22:38,929
Many VI Ps and government offilcials
will attend the opening ceremony.

153
00:22:39,007 --> 00:22:40,872
You are assigned to protect them.

154
00:22:40,942 --> 00:22:43,274
Their information is in your filles.

155
00:22:43,344 --> 00:22:45,175
Make sure you're extra alert!

156
00:22:45,246 --> 00:22:46,543
Yes, sir!

157
00:22:46,614 --> 00:22:50,550
Tony Weng,
we're protecting that scum.

158
00:23:21,883 --> 00:23:23,373
Attention please!

159
00:23:23,451 --> 00:23:27,319
Will all the competitors please
assemble before the floating platform...

160
00:23:27,388 --> 00:23:29,379
for the dotting
of the dragon's eye.

161
00:23:29,457 --> 00:23:31,084
It's our pleasure to welcome...

162
00:23:31,159 --> 00:23:34,458
the president ofTung Yuan
Financial Corp., Mr. Tony Weng...

163
00:23:34,529 --> 00:23:38,590
the chairman of Rotary Club,
Mr. Peter Chu...

164
00:26:25,800 --> 00:26:28,667
Cover him up.
Keep everything under control.

165
00:26:28,736 --> 00:26:31,398
Red alert! red alert! Tony Weng's
been shot on the floating platform.

166
00:26:36,878 --> 00:26:38,743
The shot came from
around the filshing junks.

167
00:26:38,813 --> 00:26:41,179
The killer is probably nearby.

168
00:26:41,249 --> 00:26:44,218
All units!
Prepare to seal off the area.

169
00:26:48,222 --> 00:26:50,156
Mr. Weng fainted.
Everything's filne.

170
00:26:50,224 --> 00:26:51,691
Please enjoy your day.

171
00:27:27,028 --> 00:27:28,461
Chang!

172
00:30:55,570 --> 00:30:58,733
Chang, look over there!
An explosion!

173
00:30:58,806 --> 00:31:00,000
Let's check it out

174
00:31:17,525 --> 00:31:19,083
Chang, we can't lose him now!

175
00:31:59,867 --> 00:32:01,164
Freeze!

176
00:32:44,211 --> 00:32:45,473
You'll be all right.

177
00:32:47,415 --> 00:32:49,349
Don't be afraid.

178
00:32:53,888 --> 00:32:55,981
Don't cry.

179
00:33:01,996 --> 00:33:04,658
- He's down there! Step on it!
- Okay.

180
00:33:11,739 --> 00:33:15,539
- Any hospitals nearby?
- Think he's got a conscience?

181
00:33:15,609 --> 00:33:17,873
He won't let the little girl die.

182
00:33:35,863 --> 00:33:37,421
Nurse, where's casualty?

183
00:33:37,498 --> 00:33:39,329
Go down the hall.

184
00:33:44,105 --> 00:33:45,800
What happened?

185
00:33:45,873 --> 00:33:49,001
- A gunshot.
- Quickly, put her down.

186
00:33:49,076 --> 00:33:52,534
Nurse, check her blood pressure.
Prepare her for surgery.

187
00:33:52,613 --> 00:33:54,604
Oxygen mask.

188
00:33:54,682 --> 00:34:00,348
How is she?

189
00:34:00,421 --> 00:34:03,822
Blood pressure unstable.
Weak pulse.

190
00:34:03,891 --> 00:34:06,189
Blood pressure low.

191
00:34:10,164 --> 00:34:12,325
- Have you seen a man carrying a child?
- He went to casualty.

192
00:34:12,399 --> 00:34:13,889
- Detain anyone suspicious.
- Yes, sir!

193
00:34:13,968 --> 00:34:17,096
Are you related to the patient?
How was she wounded?

194
00:34:17,171 --> 00:34:19,605
Sir, you can't leave now!

195
00:34:19,673 --> 00:34:22,039
I have to register your name.

196
00:34:23,110 --> 00:34:25,044
Where is he?

197
00:34:37,691 --> 00:34:40,785
I'm an inspector.
Just continue.

198
00:34:51,505 --> 00:34:54,440
- Right, nurses, ignore them.
- Yes.

199
00:34:55,176 --> 00:34:58,475
Don't disturb the doctor.
Put your guns down.

200
00:35:45,860 --> 00:35:47,327
- What happened?
- There was a gunshot.

201
00:35:47,394 --> 00:35:49,225
- Where?
- Over there.

202
00:35:50,531 --> 00:35:51,555
Get everybody out.

203
00:36:13,554 --> 00:36:15,818
I'll call H.Q

204
00:36:15,890 --> 00:36:19,451
- Any progress in the Weng case?
- No, none at all.

205
00:36:19,526 --> 00:36:21,994
I nearly got the suspect,
but he escaped.

206
00:36:22,062 --> 00:36:26,192
Where's your razor sharp
intuition?

207
00:36:26,267 --> 00:36:28,735
Many people want me to fail...

208
00:36:28,802 --> 00:36:31,828
so this case means a lot to me.

209
00:36:31,906 --> 00:36:34,739
I don't need you letting me down.

210
00:36:34,808 --> 00:36:37,971
You always were a pain in the ass.

211
00:36:38,045 --> 00:36:41,242
Do me a favor and prove me wrong.

212
00:36:41,315 --> 00:36:44,284
Sir, I do nothing for nobody.

213
00:36:45,352 --> 00:36:47,650
I'll get the murderer.

214
00:36:47,721 --> 00:36:50,554
You'll get your promotion.

215
00:36:50,624 --> 00:36:53,525
I hope you don't forget
who helped you reach the top.

216
00:36:57,197 --> 00:37:00,030
I want you to draw the suspect.
Try to bring him to life.

217
00:37:00,935 --> 00:37:02,766
He's over 30.

218
00:37:02,836 --> 00:37:05,532
He looks determined...

219
00:37:05,606 --> 00:37:07,699
without being ruthless.

220
00:37:08,909 --> 00:37:11,571
There's something heroic about him.

221
00:37:14,882 --> 00:37:17,544
He doesn't look like a killer.

222
00:37:19,320 --> 00:37:21,254
He comes across so calm...

223
00:37:22,723 --> 00:37:25,157
acts like he has a dream...

224
00:37:25,225 --> 00:37:27,386
eyes full of passion.

225
00:38:18,212 --> 00:38:20,203
- Hello.
- It's me, Jeffrey.

226
00:38:20,280 --> 00:38:22,214
Jeffrey?
Why haven't you left town?

227
00:38:22,282 --> 00:38:24,216
I want my money now.

228
00:38:28,122 --> 00:38:30,886
I want it tonight. Tonight!

229
00:38:30,958 --> 00:38:33,449
Sure, I'll bring it tonight.

230
00:38:43,237 --> 00:38:44,169
Mr. Weng.

231
00:38:44,238 --> 00:38:47,139
You should let me handleJeffrey.

232
00:38:47,207 --> 00:38:49,141
He's my responsibility.

233
00:38:49,209 --> 00:38:52,178
- What if he squeals on me?
- He wouldn't.

234
00:38:52,246 --> 00:38:55,340
I don't trust anyone,
including you!

235
00:38:58,652 --> 00:39:02,679
I know the rules of the game.
I'll keep my word.

236
00:39:02,756 --> 00:39:05,987
Forget the rules.

237
00:39:06,060 --> 00:39:09,359
I want him dead
because he exposed his identity.

238
00:39:09,430 --> 00:39:12,399
I'm the boss now,
and you'll do things my way.

239
00:39:12,466 --> 00:39:15,663
Okay, you kill him for me.

240
00:39:15,736 --> 00:39:21,265
Ifyou blow it,
you're dead meat.

241
00:39:21,341 --> 00:39:23,502
I paid you well enough.

242
00:39:45,099 --> 00:39:46,930
Eddie, this could be a lead.

243
00:39:47,000 --> 00:39:51,699
Six months ago, Weng's partner, Chu,
was cut down in Club Nine.

244
00:39:51,772 --> 00:39:55,640
The killer was never caught...

245
00:39:55,709 --> 00:39:58,177
but he accidentally blinded a singer.

246
00:39:58,245 --> 00:40:00,679
What was her name?

247
00:40:00,747 --> 00:40:01,771
Jenny.

248
00:40:02,883 --> 00:40:05,351
She hasn't recovered yet.

249
00:40:06,787 --> 00:40:11,884
Life's cheap.
It only takes one bullet.

250
00:40:14,962 --> 00:40:16,896
He's no ordinary assassin.

251
00:40:18,765 --> 00:40:21,256
I hope we're just looking
for one man.

252
00:40:21,335 --> 00:40:23,963
If I'm not mistaken...

253
00:40:24,037 --> 00:40:26,870
this man is not
a cold-blooded murderer.

254
00:40:26,940 --> 00:40:29,534
It only takes one bullet,
cold-blooded or not.

255
00:40:29,610 --> 00:40:32,738
He risked his life
to save the little girl.

256
00:40:35,182 --> 00:40:37,980
And if he did hurt
the singer by accident...

257
00:40:40,754 --> 00:40:42,585
he's probably contacted her.

258
00:40:42,656 --> 00:40:45,716
Ifwe meet again

259
00:40:45,792 --> 00:40:49,421
We'll filnd out where we stand

260
00:40:49,496 --> 00:40:55,162
But perhaps there will be
no tomorrow

261
00:40:56,603 --> 00:41:03,941
Only time will tell

262
00:41:07,614 --> 00:41:10,208
-Jeffrey?
- I'm notJeffrey.

263
00:41:12,486 --> 00:41:16,013
I'm sorry.
I don't see too well.

264
00:41:16,089 --> 00:41:18,114
I mistook you for my friend.

265
00:41:19,359 --> 00:41:23,125
It's a beautiful song.
Could you sing it again?

266
00:41:23,197 --> 00:41:25,757
