or for my enemy.

292
00:46:26,099 --> 00:46:30,502
It'sJohnny Weng,
Tony Weng's nephew.

293
00:46:30,570 --> 00:46:34,438
He wants you dead.
He hired you to kill his uncle.

294
00:47:08,241 --> 00:47:09,970
Do you really
have one last bullet?

295
00:47:22,756 --> 00:47:27,193
Jeffrey, thank you for sparing me.

296
00:47:29,996 --> 00:47:31,861
We're in the same boat now.

297
00:47:32,999 --> 00:47:34,660
There's no way out for us.

298
00:47:36,503 --> 00:47:38,596
Don't let me see you again.

299
00:47:43,810 --> 00:47:45,744
Inspector Li!

300
00:47:47,847 --> 00:47:50,782
Five dead witnesses.

301
00:48:21,615 --> 00:48:23,810
- It was him.
- Are you sure?

302
00:48:23,883 --> 00:48:27,319
Show his picture.
Ask the neighbors if he was here.

303
00:48:28,722 --> 00:48:30,155
Okay.

304
00:48:32,659 --> 00:48:35,822
No regrets

305
00:48:35,895 --> 00:48:38,921
No remorse

306
00:48:38,999 --> 00:48:41,991
Let bygones be bygones

307
00:48:42,869 --> 00:48:46,930
No signs of melancholy

308
00:48:48,008 --> 00:48:52,809
No tears of self-pity

309
00:48:52,879 --> 00:48:56,440
I don't care about what's
right or wrong

310
00:48:56,516 --> 00:48:59,349
I'm not sentimental about the past

311
00:48:59,419 --> 00:49:03,185
Just set me free from this reverie

312
00:49:03,256 --> 00:49:08,023
For the pain lingers on

313
00:49:08,094 --> 00:49:12,224
It dwells deep in my heart and soul

314
00:49:12,298 --> 00:49:16,325
Only time will tell

315
00:49:16,403 --> 00:49:22,399
Ifwe are meant for each other

316
00:49:23,576 --> 00:49:27,171
My tears and laughter
are my own indulgence

317
00:49:27,247 --> 00:49:31,809
Inspector, you hit the nail on the head.
The neighbors say he lives here.

318
00:49:39,025 --> 00:49:40,390
Are you nuts?

319
00:50:13,960 --> 00:50:15,325
Jenny!

320
00:50:15,395 --> 00:50:18,023
Jeffrey, is that you?

321
00:50:18,098 --> 00:50:20,032
Why don't you come back?

322
00:50:20,100 --> 00:50:22,193
I'll be back this morning.

323
00:50:22,268 --> 00:50:24,361
We're moving to a new home.

324
00:50:24,437 --> 00:50:26,337
Why?

325
00:50:26,406 --> 00:50:29,739
I thought you loved
to live by the sea.

326
00:50:29,809 --> 00:50:31,299
I do.

327
00:50:32,378 --> 00:50:34,369
Beautiful sea breezes.

328
00:50:34,447 --> 00:50:36,415
I can imagine the view
of the clear blue sky...

329
00:50:36,483 --> 00:50:38,974
and the deep blue sea.

330
00:50:39,052 --> 00:50:41,748
Great! Pack your things
and wait for me.

331
00:50:43,056 --> 00:50:44,819
I'll be here.

332
00:50:58,605 --> 00:51:01,506
Why didn't you leave Hong Kong
immediately?

333
00:51:01,574 --> 00:51:03,542
What stopped you?

334
00:51:19,025 --> 00:51:21,186
- Are you the new janitor?
- Yes.

335
00:51:21,261 --> 00:51:23,161
You're doing a lousy job.

336
00:51:23,229 --> 00:51:25,288
This is a filre escape.

337
00:51:25,365 --> 00:51:29,131
Look, there's garbage everywhere.
What if there's a filre?

338
00:51:29,202 --> 00:51:31,568
I can't fly away like a phoenix.

339
00:51:31,638 --> 00:51:35,005
I pay my monthly maintenance fee.

340
00:51:35,074 --> 00:51:38,942
If I filnd you goofilng off again,
I'll fille a complaint.

341
00:51:39,012 --> 00:51:43,142
Don't leave any garbage here.
Move it all away. Shit!

342
00:52:14,814 --> 00:52:17,282
Jeffrey, you're back.

343
00:52:17,350 --> 00:52:19,147
Yes, Jenny.

344
00:52:22,856 --> 00:52:24,050
Are you with a friend?

345
00:52:25,892 --> 00:52:28,759
Yes, he's my old football buddy.

346
00:52:30,563 --> 00:52:33,396
We grew up
in the same squatter area.

347
00:52:34,934 --> 00:52:37,061
Yes. He's...

348
00:52:37,136 --> 00:52:38,728
I'm Dumbo,
he's Mickey Mouse.

349
00:52:40,006 --> 00:52:42,804
That's what you called
each other?

350
00:52:43,943 --> 00:52:47,208
- It's good to see you again.
- The feeling isn't mutual.

351
00:52:47,280 --> 00:52:51,307
- You're not pleased to see your friend?
- We're not that close.

352
00:52:51,384 --> 00:52:55,150
- He's been causing me a lot of trouble.
- I'm here to sort it out.

353
00:52:55,221 --> 00:52:57,314
Please sit.
I'll put on some tea.

354
00:52:57,390 --> 00:52:58,687
- Don't bother.
- No need.

355
00:52:59,559 --> 00:53:01,618
- Please be careful.
- Take care, Jenny.

356
00:53:01,694 --> 00:53:03,389
I know how to do it.
I won't hurt myself.

357
00:53:03,463 --> 00:53:06,091
Jeffrey, take care
ofyour friend, meanwhile.

358
00:53:09,302 --> 00:53:11,099
Make yourself at home, Dumbo.

359
00:53:11,170 --> 00:53:14,230
I am, Mickey Mouse.

360
00:53:14,307 --> 00:53:17,572
Ma'am, why are you so concerned
about the garbage?

361
00:53:17,644 --> 00:53:21,011
He paid me a thousand bucks
to keep you talking.

362
