Don't leave now!
I haven't had this much fun in 20 years!

363
00:53:25,785 --> 00:53:29,585
- You're going to lose this game.
- Am l? Lets wait and see.

364
00:53:29,656 --> 00:53:32,181
You're always the loser.

365
00:53:33,393 --> 00:53:36,521
Not this time.
I'm well prepared.

366
00:53:37,830 --> 00:53:39,764
Let's put your preparations
to the test.

367
00:53:42,535 --> 00:53:46,904
- Are you always so determined?
- Yes, that's my style.

368
00:53:46,973 --> 00:53:48,235
Mine too.

369
00:53:48,308 --> 00:53:51,675
So we have something in common.

370
00:53:51,744 --> 00:53:54,406
Is that what you think?

371
00:53:56,649 --> 00:53:58,480
Defilnitely.

372
00:53:59,452 --> 00:54:02,649
Have some tea while you catch up
on old times.

373
00:54:04,390 --> 00:54:06,551
Thanks, Jenny. Be careful.

374
00:54:09,495 --> 00:54:14,831
- Here's my friend's hand.
- Here's your tea.

375
00:54:17,403 --> 00:54:18,802
- Thank you.
- A pleasure.

376
00:54:18,871 --> 00:54:21,339
Is he another friend ofyours?

377
00:54:21,407 --> 00:54:25,309
No, he's the janitor. We don't have
a janitor in this building.

378
00:54:25,378 --> 00:54:27,107
Oh, he's the plumber.

379
00:54:27,180 --> 00:54:32,777
There's a burst water pipe outside.

380
00:54:32,852 --> 00:54:35,082
Your voice sounds familiar.

381
00:54:35,154 --> 00:54:36,587
Have we met before?

382
00:54:36,656 --> 00:54:39,523
I met you in the night club.

383
00:54:39,592 --> 00:54:41,924
I loved your singing, but you wouldn't
sing withoutJeffrey there.

384
00:54:41,995 --> 00:54:43,690
Oh, I remember.

385
00:54:43,763 --> 00:54:45,697
What a coincidence.

386
00:54:45,765 --> 00:54:48,859
Dumbo, take care ofJenny for a while.
I'm going to the bathroom.

387
00:54:48,935 --> 00:54:50,630
So am l.

388
00:54:50,703 --> 00:54:54,662
There's a second bathroom
in the bedroom.

389
00:54:54,741 --> 00:54:58,177
Jenny, there's a rat in the kitchen!
I'll catch it.

390
00:55:32,712 --> 00:55:36,170
Hey! Don't shoot! It's me!

391
00:55:36,249 --> 00:55:39,685
Somebody's aiming at my ass
from below!

392
00:56:06,312 --> 00:56:09,338
What happened?
Where'sJeffrey?

393
00:56:11,484 --> 00:56:16,217
I know you both lied to me.
Tell me the truth!

394
00:56:16,289 --> 00:56:20,885
- Who the hell are you?
- I'm a cop.

395
00:56:23,529 --> 00:56:26,430
Jeffrey's a professional killer.
He murdered somebody.

396
00:56:26,499 --> 00:56:29,764
I've been after him for months.

397
00:56:29,836 --> 00:56:32,805
- I don't believe you!
-Jenny!

398
00:56:32,872 --> 00:56:35,568
- Listen to me, Jenny!
- No!

399
00:56:35,641 --> 00:56:38,872
-Jenny, it's true.
- Chang!

400
00:56:38,945 --> 00:56:41,971
Jenny, calm down.
Listen, please!

401
00:56:43,382 --> 00:56:44,974
Sit down.

402
00:56:49,155 --> 00:56:51,419
Six months ago...

403
00:56:51,491 --> 00:56:53,459
Jeffrey shot your face up by accident.

404
00:56:55,228 --> 00:56:57,662
Now his employer wants him dead.

405
00:56:58,698 --> 00:57:00,598
I don't believe it!

406
00:57:06,372 --> 00:57:09,432
I'd like to help,
but I can't, in my position.

407
00:57:11,377 --> 00:57:15,040
I hope you'll cooperate with us.

408
00:57:15,114 --> 00:57:19,983
Jenny, we're using you as bait.

409
00:57:20,052 --> 00:57:22,680
It can bringJeffrey in this time.

410
00:57:22,755 --> 00:57:24,689
I'll save his life for you.

411
00:57:26,492 --> 00:57:28,426
Otherwise, the guy who hired him
will kill him.

412
00:57:35,446 --> 00:57:37,710
Name your price.
I want him dead.

413
00:57:37,782 --> 00:57:40,478
He was recognized doing the job.

414
00:57:40,551 --> 00:57:42,815
I want him wasted,
the sooner the better.

415
00:57:42,887 --> 00:57:44,752
Deposit $ 1 00,000
into my account now...

416
00:57:44,822 --> 00:57:47,222
and $200,000 more upon completion.

417
00:57:49,460 --> 00:57:51,121
No money, no action, Mr. Weng.

418
00:57:51,195 --> 00:57:54,130
Not even if I see his filnger on
the trigger ready to blow your head off.

419
00:57:55,299 --> 00:57:57,961
- Put the hundred grand in his account.
- Yes, sir.

420
00:57:58,036 --> 00:57:59,970
Mr. Weng!
What do you want?

421
00:58:06,744 --> 00:58:09,679
You should payJeffrey,
or he might come after you.

422
00:58:11,149 --> 00:58:13,117
That's bullshit! I'm safe.

423
00:58:13,184 --> 00:58:15,482
Look at these guys.
They're killers.

424
00:58:20,692 --> 00:58:22,125
You're the boss.
You should keep your word.

425
00:58:22,193 --> 00:58:23,854
Don't talk crap.

426
00:58:23,928 --> 00:58:26,260
I won't pay him,
even ifyou beg.

427
00:58:26,330 --> 00:58:29,197
Mr. Weng, let me keep my word
and pay him what I promised.

428
00:58:30,835 --> 00:58:32,598
Then I'll bring him to you.

429
00:58:36,974 --> 00:58:39,875
Mr. Weng, if it pleases you...

430
00:58:41,312 --> 00:58:42,609
I will beg.

431
00:58:44,048 --> 00:58:45,242
Go to hell!

432
00:58:45,316 --> 00:58:47,079
Ifyou hadn't worked for my father
for so long...

433
00:58:47,151 --> 00:58:48,209
I'd have kicked the shit out ofyou!

434
00:58:48,286 --> 00:58:49,776
Who is he?

435
00:58:49,854 --> 00:58:51,219
He doesn't deserve your sympathy!

436
00:58:51,289 --> 00:58:54,725
Why are you doing all this forJeffrey?

437
00:58:54,792 --> 00:58:57,260
He's my best friend.

438
00:58:57,328 --> 00:58:59,319
Cut the crap!

439
00:59:44,142 --> 00:59:46,133
Come here now!
Mr. Weng's been shot.

440
01:00:06,597 --> 01:00:08,724
Kill him!

441
01:00:12,069 --> 01:00:13,297
Kill him!

442
01:00:13,371 --> 01:00:15,271
Don't let him go!

443
01:00:15,339 --> 01:00:17,466
- Mr. Weng, you've been hurt!
-Just kill him!

444
01:00:17,542 --> 01:00:20,705
- Let's go! You're in danger!
- Go after him!

445
01:00:54,145 --> 01:00:57,842
Ifyou consider me your friend,
kill me now.

446
01:00:59,417 --> 01:01:01,942
I loathe seeing you demean
yourself by begging.

447
01:01:09,961 --> 01:01:11,394
Though I didn't succeed...

448
01:01:11,462 --> 01:01:13,453
I risked my life trying
to get you your money!

449
01:01:15,166 --> 01:01:17,191
I could have just killed you.

450
01:01:17,268 --> 01:01:20,066
I didn't have to beg Weng
for your money.

451
01:01:20,137 --> 01:01:22,765
I'm not completely
without honor, am l?

452
01:01:46,797 --> 01:01:49,061
Our world is changing so fast.

453
01:01:51,135 --> 01:01:55,629
It never used to be like this.
Perhaps we're too nostalgic.

454
01:02:05,316 --> 01:02:07,546
Nostalgia is one of our saving graces.

455
01:02:08,986 --> 01:02:12,012
At least when I die, I'll know
I was remembered by a friend.

456
01:02:14,225 --> 01:02:16,693
Let's settle our differences
in the next life.

457
01:02:28,139 --> 01:02:30,937
Let's cancel them right now.

458
01:02:31,008 --> 01:02:33,238
That's what friends are for.

459
01:02:34,612 --> 01:02:35,544
Right?

460
01:03:19,090 --> 01:03:21,058
- A drink?
- Thank you.

461
01:03:22,326 --> 01:03:25,523
Jenny always wanted
to live by the sea.

462
01:03:27,398 --> 01:03:30,390
You've done so much for her.

463
01:03:30,468 --> 01:03:33,198
I wonder how she feels about you.

464
01:03:39,977 --> 01:03:41,501
- Hello?
-Jenny!

465
01:03:41,579 --> 01:03:45,015
Jeffrey, why did you leave
without saying good-bye?

466
01:03:45,082 --> 01:03:48,210
I'm sorry.
I had something to do.

467
01:03:48,285 --> 01:03:51,448
We have to leave tonight.

468
01:03:51,522 --> 01:03:53,956
- Tonight?
- Dr. Ho called this afternoon.

469
01:03:54,025 --> 01:03:57,654
He's reserved a pair of corneas,
but they're in Singapore.

470
01:03:57,728 --> 01:04:01,289
Ifwe're not there by midnight,
someone else gets them.

471
01:04:03,000 --> 01:04:04,558
All right, I'll take you.

472
01:04:04,635 --> 01:04:07,365
Meet me at the airport
at 7.30 tonight.

473
01:04:07,438 --> 01:04:09,372
I'll wait at the information
desk, okay?

474
01:04:09,440 --> 01:04:11,032
Of course.

475
01:04:14,612 --> 01:04:16,546
Will he come?

476
01:04:25,856 --> 01:04:27,483
Will you go?

477
01:04:31,162 --> 01:04:32,823
I trust her.

478
01:04:46,243 --> 01:04:48,074
Everybody's here. Let's go.

479
01:04:50,581 --> 01:04:52,674
How's it going?

480
01:04:52,750 --> 01:04:55,184
Right. Full alert now.

481
01:04:56,754 --> 01:04:58,745
I want you to check
every inch of this place.

482
01:04:58,823 --> 01:05:00,654
Everything's ready.
He'll never get away.

483
01:05:28,419 --> 01:05:30,944
Don't worry.

484
01:05:31,021 --> 01:05:35,754
We'll take care of everything
while you're away.

485
01:05:35,826 --> 01:05:37,054
Thank you.

486
01:05:39,230 --> 01:05:41,391
Have a nice trip.

487
01:05:42,867 --> 01:05:47,201
While I am gone, take good care
of the company business.

488
01:05:47,271 --> 01:05:51,537
Please take care.

489
01:05:54,111 --> 01:05:55,976
Jeffrey!

490
01:05:56,046 --> 01:05:58,606
Get away from here! Run!

491
01:05:58,682 --> 01:05:59,671
She's crazy!

492
01:06:01,552 --> 01:06:03,281
Jeffrey!

493
01:06:03,354 --> 01:06:07,381
Jeffrey, the cops are everywhere!
Run away!

494
01:06:07,458 --> 01:06:11,724
Jeffrey, the cops want you!

495
01:06:11,795 --> 01:06:15,162
Don't come near me!

496
01:06:15,232 --> 01:06:19,362
Jeffrey, are you there? Run!
Don't let them catch you!

497
01:06:33,684 --> 01:06:35,379
Jeffrey, run!

498
01:06:40,257 --> 01:06:42,225
The cops are after you!

499
01:06:43,627 --> 01:06:45,788
Freeze!

500
01:06:47,364 --> 01:06:49,195
Jeffrey, the cops are all around!

501
01:06:51,969 --> 01:06:54,597
The cops are everywhere!

502
01:06:54,672 --> 01:06:55,366
Run!

503
01:06:58,509 --> 01:07:00,636
Jeffrey, run away!

504
01:07:02,813 --> 01:07:04,303
It's me, Jenny.

505
01:07:08,786 --> 01:07:10,583
Don't move!

506
01:07:10,654 --> 01:07:11,746
Let's go.

507
01:07:11,822 --> 01:07:14,518
What's wrong, offilcer?
Flirting isn't a crime.

508
01:07:21,465 --> 01:07:22,932
Arrest him!

509
01:07:33,811 --> 01:07:35,403
Keep clear, everyone.
Let me through.

510
01:07:51,262 --> 01:07:53,389
Open those suitcases.

511
01:07:54,665 --> 01:07:57,634
- What were you doing at the airport?
- Chasing a piece of ass.

512
01:07:57,701 --> 01:07:59,191
What's yourjob?

513
01:07:59,270 --> 01:08:04,207
