521
01:08:47,718 --> 01:08:49,652
I have some questions to ask him.

522
01:08:51,655 --> 01:08:53,350
That's none of my business.

523
01:08:54,525 --> 01:08:58,325
If the guy you're talking about
is my friend...

524
01:08:59,797 --> 01:09:02,163
he sure doesn't need your help.

525
01:09:07,571 --> 01:09:09,664
Starting now,
you're off the Weng case.

526
01:09:09,740 --> 01:09:12,072
Inspector Chan will take over.

527
01:09:12,142 --> 01:09:13,905
You're getting another case.

528
01:09:15,379 --> 01:09:17,347
- What's the reason?
- I don't trust you.

529
01:09:19,083 --> 01:09:22,678
Siding with the suspect
is not the way to catch him.

530
01:09:24,822 --> 01:09:27,552
Sir, you don't understand how I work.

531
01:09:27,624 --> 01:09:32,084
You said it!
That's why you're off the case.

532
01:09:35,499 --> 01:09:37,364
I won't give up the investigation.

533
01:09:37,434 --> 01:09:38,401
Bullshit!

534
01:09:38,469 --> 01:09:41,370
Chang, you'll be Chan's assistant.

535
01:09:43,774 --> 01:09:44,706
Yes, sir.

536
01:09:44,775 --> 01:09:46,766
Release the man you just arrested.

537
01:09:46,844 --> 01:09:48,778
Give him 24-hour surveillance.

538
01:09:48,846 --> 01:09:51,508
He'll lead us to Weng's assassin.

539
01:09:51,582 --> 01:09:55,609
- Have you got that?
- Yes, sir.

540
01:10:18,542 --> 01:10:20,601
Will you kill again?

541
01:10:27,217 --> 01:10:30,050
I thought the people I killed
deserved to die.

542
01:10:34,491 --> 01:10:37,483
Now I believe everybody has
the right to live.

543
01:10:37,561 --> 01:10:40,724
No, I won't kill again.
I hope I can keep my promise.

544
01:14:03,900 --> 01:14:05,492
I've been followed.

545
01:14:05,569 --> 01:14:07,833
Weng's men, and the cops too.

546
01:14:09,940 --> 01:14:11,134
Don't worry, I lost them.

547
01:14:13,677 --> 01:14:16,145
Weng hired Paul Yau to waste you.

548
01:14:16,213 --> 01:14:20,343
Don't worry,
you can use my guns and ammo.

549
01:14:24,721 --> 01:14:28,213
- Where are you going?
- To get your money off Weng.

550
01:14:30,227 --> 01:14:31,353
I'll meet you in the church.

551
01:14:33,964 --> 01:14:37,331
- Are you going alone?
- Yes, of course.

552
01:14:37,401 --> 01:14:39,460
I must keep my promise.

553
01:14:40,737 --> 01:14:43,467
Weng won't hurt me.
I still deserve some respect.

554
01:14:45,809 --> 01:14:50,109
Sidney, I don't need the money.

555
01:14:51,348 --> 01:14:52,610
I do need your friendship.

556
01:15:10,267 --> 01:15:13,794
Chang! Chang!

557
01:15:19,276 --> 01:15:23,736
I followed him to 6 Horizon Drive.

558
01:15:23,814 --> 01:15:27,341
I almost got him.

559
01:15:27,417 --> 01:15:28,714
I know.

560
01:15:28,785 --> 01:15:30,116
I could have... got him.

561
01:15:30,187 --> 01:15:33,213
Don't worry, I'll filnd him.
Chang, don't worry.

562
01:15:36,193 --> 01:15:37,387
Eddie.

563
01:15:38,562 --> 01:15:41,463
You can't win all the time.

564
01:15:41,531 --> 01:15:46,230
But you can't lose forever, either.

565
01:15:52,509 --> 01:15:56,001
Chang... Chang...

566
01:16:15,432 --> 01:16:17,593
Inspector Li,
did he give us anything?

567
01:16:19,336 --> 01:16:20,963
Go ask him yourself!

568
01:17:44,521 --> 01:17:49,686
-Jeffrey!
-Jenny, what is it?

569
01:17:49,759 --> 01:17:53,559
Why is it so dark this morning?

570
01:17:53,630 --> 01:17:55,928
It's just a cloudy day.

571
01:17:59,169 --> 01:18:02,229
Relax, it'll be all right.

572
01:18:03,673 --> 01:18:05,971
- Are we leaving today?
- Yes.

573
01:18:09,279 --> 01:18:10,769
Freeze!

574
01:18:10,847 --> 01:18:12,974
Who is it?

575
01:18:13,049 --> 01:18:14,983
It's Mickey Mouse.

576
01:18:15,051 --> 01:18:16,313
What does he want?

577
01:18:16,386 --> 01:18:18,320
He's come to say good-bye.

578
01:18:21,825 --> 01:18:23,087
What are you waiting for?

579
01:18:23,159 --> 01:18:26,094
I'm a cop.
I don't shoot people in the back.

580
01:18:26,162 --> 01:18:28,130
Another way we're the same.

581
01:18:28,198 --> 01:18:30,758
No, we're not the same!

582
01:18:30,834 --> 01:18:32,825
I uphold the law,
and you break it!

583
01:18:34,237 --> 01:18:38,003
Chang died because ofyou.
I swore I'd get you this time.

584
01:18:42,712 --> 01:18:46,273
I'm sorry, but I won't
let you lock me up.

585
01:18:48,151 --> 01:18:52,588
Ifyou must take revenge
for your friend, shoot me now.

586
01:18:52,656 --> 01:18:54,590
Don't force me to kill you!

587
01:19:13,410 --> 01:19:16,379
- You'd really kill me?
- I won't let you go this time.

588
01:19:16,446 --> 01:19:18,175
Go ahead.

589
01:19:18,248 --> 01:19:20,443
You can't win all the time.

590
01:19:20,517 --> 01:19:23,680
Jeffrey, where are you?

591
01:19:23,753 --> 01:19:26,586
Where is he?

592
01:19:26,656 --> 01:19:29,454
Right in front ofyou.

593
01:19:29,526 --> 01:19:31,619
- Don't take him away.
-Jenny!

594
01:19:31,695 --> 01:19:34,027
Jeffrey's promised me
he'll never kill again.

595
01:19:34,097 --> 01:19:36,361
Put that gun down.
Jenny, put that gun down.

596
01:19:36,433 --> 01:19:39,800
Not unless he leaves us alone.

597
01:19:39,869 --> 01:19:43,532
I beg you, please, let us go.
I'll never let you arrest him!

598
01:19:45,775 --> 01:19:48,471
Did I kill him? ls he dead?

599
01:19:48,545 --> 01:19:52,345
I didn't mean to kill him.
I didn't mean it.

600
01:19:52,415 --> 01:19:54,542
He's all right.

601
01:19:54,617 --> 01:19:56,710
I didn't mean to...

602
01:20:00,256 --> 01:20:01,348
He's filne.

603
01:21:07,357 --> 01:21:09,484
Calm down, be brave!

604
01:21:09,559 --> 01:21:11,151
- You stay there!
-Jeffrey!

605
01:21:37,087 --> 01:21:39,419
Let's get out of here.
Then you can arrest me.

606
01:21:46,863 --> 01:21:49,331
Let's getJenny out of here.

607
01:21:50,033 --> 01:21:51,967
The car's outside.

608
01:22:25,301 --> 01:22:27,064
Come on!

609
01:23:13,249 --> 01:23:15,979
I won't let you put me behind bars!

610
01:23:16,052 --> 01:23:18,452
Throw the gun down.

611
01:23:24,027 --> 01:23:25,551
You wouldn't kill a cop.

612
01:24:11,574 --> 01:24:13,269
Thank you.

613
01:24:15,178 --> 01:24:16,736
You could have killed me
with one shot.

614
01:24:17,880 --> 01:24:21,145
I don't kill anybody until I know
they are the real enemy.

615
01:24:21,217 --> 01:24:25,916
- Do you really know me?
- Fate controls everything.

616
01:24:28,057 --> 01:24:33,085
The only person who really knows me
turns out to be a cop.

617
01:24:33,162 --> 01:24:34,652
You could always give yourself up.

618
01:24:37,066 --> 01:24:42,902
No. I made a promise.
I keep my word.

619
01:24:42,972 --> 01:24:47,602
Sometimes, I really envy you,
your freedom.

620
01:24:47,677 --> 01:24:50,305
It's something I don't have.

621
01:24:50,380 --> 01:24:53,008
I believe in justice,
but nobody trusts me.

622
01:24:54,550 --> 01:24:55,812
I have the same problem.

623
01:24:59,322 --> 01:25:00,812
You're an unusual cop.

624
01:25:02,592 --> 01:25:04,059
And you're an unusual killer.

625
01:25:07,897 --> 01:25:10,491
I'm sorry to drag you
into this mess.

626
01:25:10,566 --> 01:25:12,193
Tell me, who's behind all this?

627
01:25:12,268 --> 01:25:15,601
That's not my game.
I play by the rules.

628
01:25:17,273 --> 01:25:20,800
I knew you would never tell me.

629
01:25:20,877 --> 01:25:23,812
Take care ofJenny.

630
01:25:23,880 --> 01:25:27,077
Weng won't stop until he kills you.
You'd better let me arrest you.

631
01:25:51,974 --> 01:25:53,236
We'll stay here tonight.

632
01:25:53,309 --> 01:25:57,075
Sidney will bring me my money,
and we'll leave tomorrow.

633
01:25:57,146 --> 01:25:59,239
I'm scared those gangsters
will filnd us here.

634
01:26:01,651 --> 01:26:03,915
Don't worry.

635
01:26:03,986 --> 01:26:06,750
This place isn't easy to filnd.

636
01:26:09,959 --> 01:26:12,291
Why is it so dark?

637
01:26:15,164 --> 01:26:17,098
I can hardly see anything.

638
01:26:18,801 --> 01:26:23,738
Jeffrey, turn on the lights.
Why don't you turn on the lights?

639
01:26:28,411 --> 01:26:29,969
Jeffrey.

640
01:26:37,854 --> 01:26:39,515
Please turn them on.

641
01:26:39,589 --> 01:26:42,217
There's been a power failure.

642
01:26:48,798 --> 01:26:51,062
Will your friend come back
with the money?

643
01:26:53,269 --> 01:26:55,203
I'm sure he will.

644
01:26:56,539 --> 01:26:58,473
I'm sure he will.

645
01:27:01,644 --> 01:27:03,271
Boss.

646
01:27:03,346 --> 01:27:05,576
Here's the $ 1 00,000.
Please check it.

647
01:27:05,648 --> 01:27:06,672
You think he can kill Jeffrey?

648
01:27:20,096 --> 01:27:23,293
Boss, Sidney Fung is here.

649
01:27:24,300 --> 01:27:26,530
What if he betrays you again?

650
01:27:32,442 --> 01:27:36,936
I'd still consider him my friend.
He was so good to me.

651
01:27:41,284 --> 01:27:45,050
- Where isJeffrey's money?
- Where the hell is he?

652
01:27:45,121 --> 01:27:46,782
I wish that I had a friend like you.

653
01:27:49,559 --> 01:27:52,119
You will, one of these days.

654
01:28:07,977 --> 01:28:09,501
Drop your guns!

655
01:28:14,150 --> 01:28:15,481
Your right hand still works?

656
01:28:15,551 --> 01:28:18,645
Well enough.
It's still fast and accurate.

657
01:28:18,721 --> 01:28:22,418
You've got no way out.
Why are you doing this?

658
01:28:22,492 --> 01:28:23,959
You tell me,
what's the alternative?

659
01:28:25,661 --> 01:28:28,494
- Where's the money?
- Give it to me!

660
01:28:43,346 --> 01:28:47,305
I'm one step ahead.
Why didn't you shoot me in the head?

661
01:28:48,718 --> 01:28:50,948
Maybe I'm no longer a professional.

662
01:28:54,590 --> 01:28:57,388
I wish I could start all over again.

663
01:28:58,995 --> 01:29:00,792
It's a pity...

664
01:29:05,601 --> 01:29:08,069
- Give me the cash.
- Where isJeffrey?

665
01:29:08,137 --> 01:29:10,628
Give me the money filrst.

666
01:29:14,977 --> 01:29:16,604
We owe it to him.

667
01:29:18,180 --> 01:29:19,112
Hypocrite!

668
01:29:24,320 --> 01:29:26,811
Do all killers
have a sense of honor?

669
01:29:26,889 --> 01:29:30,552
The world has changed.
Honor is now a dirty word.

670
01:29:34,730 --> 01:29:36,994
Sidney, sometimes I think
you're not human.

671
01:29:37,066 --> 01:29:39,034
You're more like a dog.

672
01:29:42,538 --> 01:29:45,632
At least we have
one thing in common:

673
01:29:45,708 --> 01:29:47,938
We both use guns for a living.

674
01:29:50,479 --> 01:29:53,243
But our motivations are different.

675
01:29:53,316 --> 01:29:54,977
Right?

676
01:29:57,787 --> 01:30:00,449
In some ways
dogs are superior to men.

677
01:30:09,999 --> 01:30:13,264
Ifyou don't tell me whereJeffrey is,
this is your funeral.

678
01:30:13,336 --> 01:30:15,429
Throw this garbage away.

679
01:30:36,459 --> 01:30:39,019
- Give me the money!
- Are you sure you still got bullets?

680
01:30:40,563 --> 01:30:42,053
You wanna bet?

681
01:30:43,432 --> 01:30:47,300
Jeffrey said,
always save one last slug.

682
01:30:47,370 --> 01:30:49,065
Either for yourself,
or your enemy.

683
01:31:03,786 --> 01:31:05,151
Hurry!

684
01:31:07,623 --> 01:31:09,250
Turn around!

685
01:31:18,334 --> 01:31:20,234
Goddamn it!

686
01:31:26,042 --> 01:31:27,168
Get him!

687
01:31:35,284 --> 01:31:38,583
Promise me one thing:

688
01:31:38,654 --> 01:31:40,588
If I don't make it,
take me to a hospital.

689
01:31:42,425 --> 01:31:46,384
Have them save my corneas forJenny.

690
01:31:48,597 --> 01:31:50,121
If that's impossible...

691
01:31:51,000 --> 01:31:53,560
organize my money
and send her abroad for surgery.

692
01:31:57,006 --> 01:31:58,132
Don't think like that.

693
01:32:02,078 --> 01:32:06,879
It's the filrst decent thing
I've ever done.

694
01:32:06,949 --> 01:32:09,042
Will you help me?

695
01:32:43,486 --> 01:32:44,510
What's that noise?

696
01:32:46,555 --> 01:32:48,489
Who is it, Jeffrey?

697
01:32:59,502 --> 01:33:01,265
Sidney.

698
01:33:07,343 --> 01:33:12,610
Here's your money.
I fought for it like a man.

699
01:33:17,019 --> 01:33:20,955
This is my last tribute to a friend.

700
01:33:22,391 --> 01:33:25,224
Sidney, you didn't have to do this.

701
01:33:42,478 --> 01:33:43,911
He said I was a dog.

702
01:33:45,781 --> 01:33:50,480
Now I'm not sure
if I'm human or a dog.

703
01:33:50,553 --> 01:33:53,078
Sidney, nobody can call you a dog.

704
01:33:55,591 --> 01:33:57,081
Sidney!

705
01:34:01,263 --> 01:34:02,662
Sidney!

706
01:34:10,506 --> 01:34:12,440
Sidney!

707
01:34:15,878 --> 01:34:17,368
Am I a dog?

708
01:34:19,348 --> 01:34:25,583
No, you're not a dog.
You're a great man!

709
01:34:25,654 --> 01:34:29,613
We're outmoded characters.
We're outcasts.

710
01:34:31,193 --> 01:34:34,185
I don't want to die like a dog.

711
01:34:36,899 --> 01:34:41,768
But you see,
I didn't keep one last bullet.

712
01:34:44,640 --> 01:34:46,369
I have one.

713
01:35:31,787 --> 01:35:33,379
-Jeffrey!
-Jenny, don't move!

714
01:35:33,455 --> 01:35:35,389
Don't leave me alone!

715
01:35:35,457 --> 01:35:39,416
- What'll you do?
- Storm my way out!

716
01:35:39,495 --> 01:35:43,591
Don't kill anymore, please!
Give up your guns and come with me.

717
01:35:43,666 --> 01:35:48,262
What? You saw me kill Sidney.

718
01:35:48,337 --> 01:35:50,396
He was my best friend!

719
01:35:50,472 --> 01:35:53,066
And you dare tell me to surrender?

720
01:35:55,577 --> 01:35:58,375
When Chang died,
I swore I'd kill you.

721
01:35:59,982 --> 01:36:02,542
But now I don't want you dead.

722
01:36:02,618 --> 01:36:05,280
Get out of here with Jenny.

723
01:36:05,354 --> 01:36:06,981
How?

724
01:36:07,056 --> 01:36:09,490
They'll chase me
to the ends of the earth!

725
01:36:09,558 --> 01:36:12,288
I have nowhere to go!

726
01:36:12,361 --> 01:36:15,455
Get out there
and say you're a cop.

727
01:36:15,531 --> 01:36:18,295
See if they give up their guns!

728
01:36:36,118 --> 01:36:37,380
Jenny!

729
01:36:43,959 --> 01:36:46,450
Jeffrey!

730
01:37:02,311 --> 01:37:03,835
Dumbo!

731
01:37:03,912 --> 01:37:05,607
Thanks, Mickey Mouse!

732
01:37:23,632 --> 01:37:25,566
I owe you.

733
01:37:26,935 --> 01:37:29,870
You owe me nothing.
This is a gift of friendship.

734
01:37:29,938 --> 01:37:31,496
Good luck!

735
01:38:41,310 --> 01:38:43,335
Jenny, take cover!

736
01:38:46,515 --> 01:38:48,346
Don't move!

737
01:38:51,920 --> 01:38:53,012
Jenny!

738
01:38:53,922 --> 01:38:55,890
Jenny!

739
01:40:24,112 --> 01:40:25,079
Dumbo!

740
01:40:25,914 --> 01:40:28,405
- Give me a gun!
- Here!

741
01:40:52,808 --> 01:40:54,469
How good a shot are you?

742
01:40:54,543 --> 01:40:56,977
I'm a cop.
I have to be good!

743
01:41:31,546 --> 01:41:35,107
We've been through so much,
and I don't even know your name.

744
01:41:36,151 --> 01:41:37,175
Is it important?

745
01:41:37,252 --> 01:41:41,348
Whether we win or lose,
you won't be around.

746
01:41:41,423 --> 01:41:45,018
I'd like to have a name
to remember you by.

747
01:41:45,093 --> 01:41:47,721
Would you rather see me dead
or set free?

748
01:41:48,997 --> 01:41:51,465
Neither, if fate spares us.

749
01:41:53,168 --> 01:41:55,102
You're a hell of a good friend.

750
01:41:56,238 --> 01:41:58,172
Just remember me as Mickey Mouse.
Why not?

751
01:42:57,366 --> 01:43:00,301
Leave her alone!
She's innocent!

752
01:43:20,489 --> 01:43:24,323
Drop your gun!
You heard me, hurry up!

753
01:43:25,360 --> 01:43:26,486
Jeffrey!

754
01:43:28,263 --> 01:43:30,823
Where are you, Jeffrey?

755
01:43:30,899 --> 01:43:35,768
Don't be afraid, Jenny.
I'm in front ofyou.

756
01:43:35,837 --> 01:43:37,964
Drop your gun!

757
01:43:40,409 --> 01:43:41,899
Jenny, don't move an inch!

758
01:43:43,845 --> 01:43:45,142
Don't hurt her.

759
01:43:45,213 --> 01:43:49,445
I won't hurt her.
I'll just kill her!

760
01:43:49,518 --> 01:43:50,780
Release her!

761
01:43:54,823 --> 01:43:56,848
- Let her go, Johnny!
- No way!

762
01:44:03,632 --> 01:44:04,792
What if I don't?

763
01:44:12,274 --> 01:44:14,606
Like I said, drop your guns!

764
01:44:25,587 --> 01:44:29,489
Dumbo.

765
01:44:31,026 --> 01:44:33,654
Will you do what you promised?

766
01:44:35,764 --> 01:44:36,958
No problem.

767
01:44:39,134 --> 01:44:42,535
Remember, there's always a friend
to back you up.

768
01:44:52,914 --> 01:44:55,747
Drop the guns,
or I'll kill her!

769
01:45:15,337 --> 01:45:16,599
Drop your gun, idiot!

770
01:46:01,816 --> 01:46:02,942
Jeffrey!

771
01:46:15,964 --> 01:46:17,761
Jeffrey!

772
01:46:41,256 --> 01:46:45,249
-Jeffrey!
-Jenny!

773
01:46:46,261 --> 01:46:50,129
Jeffrey, where are you?

774
01:46:57,906 --> 01:46:59,601
Jeffrey!

775
01:47:39,881 --> 01:47:41,815
Jeffrey!

776
01:47:49,124 --> 01:47:51,854
- Freeze! Don't move!
- Okay, okay, I surrender.

777
01:47:51,926 --> 01:47:54,394
I'll cooperate.
Arrest me, please!

778
01:47:58,299 --> 01:48:00,164
You're an unusual cop.

779
01:48:00,235 --> 01:48:01,896
And you're an unusual killer.

780
01:48:04,606 --> 01:48:07,632
I believe in justice,
but nobody trusts me.

781
01:48:09,411 --> 01:48:10,571
